n| <ref name=\"Xdp\">{{cite web |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=foxmarvel18b.htm |title=Dark Phoenix (2019) |work=Box Office Mojo |accessdate=August 15, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"DPBudget\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/box-office/box-office-dark-phoenix-secret-life-of-pets-2-opening-weekend-1203232810/ |title=''Dark Phoenix'' Takes on ''Secret Life of Pets 2'' in Summer Box Office Battle |last=Rubin |first=Rebecca |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=June 5, 2019 |accessdate=June 5, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\"|Total\n! ${{val|fmt=commas|{{#expr:157299717<!--XM-->+214949694<!--X2-->+234362462<!--X:TLS-->+179883157<!--XO:W-->+146408305<!--X:FC-->+132556852<!--TW-->+233921534<!--X:DOFP-->+363070709<!--D-->+155442489<!--X:A-->+226277068<!--L-->+324591735<!--DP2-->+65795828}}}}\n! ${{val|fmt=commas|{{#expr:139039810<!--XM-->+192761855<!--X2-->+224997093<!--X:TLS-->+193179707<!--XO:W-->+207215819<!--X:FC-->+282271394<!--TW-->+513941241<!--X:DOFP-->+420042270<!--D-->+388492298<!--X:A-->+392744368<!--L-->+460455185<!--DP2-->+186597000}}}}\n! ${{val|fmt=commas|{{#expr:296339527<!--XM-->+407711549<!--X2-->+459359555<!--X:TLS-->+373062864<!--XO:W-->+353624124<!--X:FC-->+414828246<!--TW-->+747862775<!--X:DOFP-->+783112979<!--D-->+543934787<!--X:A-->+619021436<!--L-->+785046920<!--DP2-->+252392828}}}}\n! colspan=\"2\" |\n! {{nowrap|$1.668{{nbsp}}billion}}\n!<ref name=\"TotalBOM\">{{cite web |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/franchises/chart/?id=xmen.htm |title=X-Men Movies at the Box Office |work=Box Office Mojo |accessdate=February 4, 2019 |url-status= dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170228123001/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/franchises/chart/?id=xmen.htm |archive-date=February 28, 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\nThe first three ''X-Men'' films and ''Deadpool'' set opening records in North America: ''X-Men'' had the highest July opening yet,<ref>{{cite web |first=Brandon |last=Gray |title=Weekend Box Office |work=Box Office Mojo |date=July 17, 2000 |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=1126&p=.htm |accessdate=August 3, 2007 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071001023213/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=1126&p=.htm |archive-date=October 1, 2007}}</ref> while ''X2'' and ''X-Men: The Last Stand'' earned the fourth-highest opening weekends yet and ''Deadpool'' got the largest opening weekend in February.<ref>{{cite web |first=Brandon |last=Gray |title='X2' Evolves Past Predecessor in Stellar Summer Kick-Off |work=Box Office Mojo |date=May 5, 2003 |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=1240&p=.htm |accessdate=August 3, 2007 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071001001737/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=1240&p=.htm |archive-date=October 1, 2007}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Brandon |last=Gray |title='X-Men' Marvels with Memorial Record |work=Box Office Mojo |date=May 30, 2006 |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=2078&p=.htm |accessdate=August 3, 2007 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070626135108/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=2078&p=.htm |archive-date=June 26, 2007}}</ref><ref name=\"Deadpool Records\">{{cite web |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=4156&p=.htm |title=Record Breaker: A Look at the Box Office Records 'Deadpool' Has Already Broken |last=Brevet |first=Brad |date=February 11, 2006 |accessdate=February 16, 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160216043446/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=4156&p=.htm |archive-date=February 16, 2016}}</ref> The records for the first three films have since been surpassed. The next three ''X-Men'' films after ''X-Men: The Last Stand'' opened lower than their predecessor and didn't set opening records.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=3706&p=.htm |title=Weekend Report: Wolverine Bleeds But Still Easily Leads |date=July 28, 2013 |accessdate=December 28, 2013 |first=Ray |last=Subers |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140112010125/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=3706&p=.htm |archive-date=January 12, 2014}}</ref> In North America, ''Deadpool'' is the highest-grossing film in the series, and it also has the highest opening weekend.<ref name=\"TotalBOM\" /><ref name=\"Deadpool Records\" /> Outside North America, ''X-Men: Days of Future Past'' has the highest opening weekend and is the highest-grossing film in the series.<ref name=\"TotalBOM\" /> Worldwide, ''Deadpool'' was the highest-grossing film in the series and the highest-grossing R-rated film of all time, before being surpassed on both records by its sequel.<ref>{{cite web |URL=http://ew.com/article/2016/03/29/deadpool-box-office-highest-grossing-r-rated-movie/ |title='Deadpool': Highest-grossing R-rated movie ever |date=March 29, 2016 |accessdate=May 23, 2017 |last=Coggan |first=Devan}}</ref>\n\nThe ''X-Men'' film series is the second highest-grossing film series based on Marvel Comics characters after the Marvel Cinematic Universe.<ref>{{cite web |title=Marvel Comics Moviesat the Box Office |work=Box Office Mojo |url= https://www.boxofficemojo.com/franchises/chart/?id=marvelcomics.htm |accessdate=March 2, 2016 |url-status= dead |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160302025723/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/franchises/chart/?id=marvelcomics.htm |archive-date=March 2, 2016}}</ref> In North America, it is the fifth-highest-grossing film series, having earned over $2.4{{nbsp}}billion.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://boxofficemojo.com/franchises/?view=Franchise&sort=sumgross&order=DESC&p=.htm |title=Movie Franchises and Brands Index |accessdate=July 4, 2019 |work=Box Office Mojo |url-status= dead |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160316033613/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/franchises/?view=Franchise&sort=sumgross&order=DESC&p=.htm |archive-date=March 16, 2016}}</ref> Worldwide, it is the [[List of highest-grossing films#Highest-grossing franchises and film series|seventh-highest-grossing film series]] of all time, having grossed over $6{{nbsp}}billion.<ref name=\"TotalBOM\" />\n\n===Critical and public response===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center; width:100%;\"\n! Film\n! [[Rotten Tomatoes]]\n! [[Metacritic]]\n! [[CinemaScore]]\n|-\n| ''X-Men''\n| 81% (172 reviews)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/xmen/ |title=X-Men |work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |publisher=[[Fandango Media]] |accessdate=June 1, 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150729012429/http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/xmen/ |archive-date=July 29, 2015}}</ref>\n| 64 (33 reviews)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/x-men |title=X-Men (2000): Reviews |work=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[CBS] |accessdate=July 27, 2013 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130609075426/http://www.metacritic.com/movie/x-men |archive-date=June 9, 2013}}</ref>\n| A\u2212<ref name=\"CinemaScore\">{{cite web |url=https://cinemascore.com/publicsearch/index/title/ |title=CinemaScore |work=[[CinemaScore]] |accessdate=November 16, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180206073531/https://cinemascore.com/publicsearch/index/title/ |archive-date=February 6, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''X2''\n| 85% (244 reviews)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/x2_xmen_united/ |title=X2: X-Men United |work=Rotten Tomatoes |publisher=Fandango Media |accessdate=June 1, 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150711082033/http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/x2_xmen_united/ |archive-date=July 11, 2015}}</ref>\n| 68 (37 reviews)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/x2 |title=X2: X-Men United (2004): Reviews |work=Metacritic |publisher=CBS |accessdate=July 27, 2013 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120627005946/http://www.metacritic.com/movie/x2 |archive-date=June 27, 2012}}</ref>\n| A<ref name=\"CinemaScore\" /