drama|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=December 27, 2019|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n| developer                = Megan Abbott & Gina Fattore<!--They chose to be credited this way according to beginning credits, per [[MOS:TV]], we go by how they chose to be credited.-->\n| based_on                 = {{based on|''[[Dare Me (novel)|Dare Me]]''|[[Megan Abbott]]}}\n| starring                 = {{plainlist|\n*[[Willa Fitzgerald]]\n*[[Herizen Guardiola]]\n*Marlo Kelly\n*[[Rob Heaps]]\n*[[Zach Roerig]]\n*[[Paul Fitzgerald (actor)|Paul Fitzgerald]]\n*[[Alison Thornton]]\n<!--Starring cast order is according to original credits (the pilot episode). Do NOT rearrange cast order, per MOS:TVCAST. In addition, new starring cast members will be at the bottom of the list.-->\n}}\n| narrated            = Herizen Guardiola\n| composer            = Jonathan Sanford\n| country             = United States\n| language            = English\n| num_seasons         = 1<!--Only increment as a new season premieres, per the documentation of the template!-->\n| num_episodes        = 10<!--Only increment as a new episode premieres, per the documentation of the template!-->\n| list_episodes       = #Episodes\n| executive_producer  = {{Plainlist|\n* Steph Green (pilot)\n* Karen Rosenfelt\n* Sarah Condon\n* [[Peter Berg]]\n* Michael Lombardo\n* Megan Abbott\n* Gina Fattore\n}}\n| producer            = {{Plainlist|\n* Dan Kaplow\n* [[Ariel Schrag]]\n* Jamie Rosengard\n}}\n| cinematography      = \n| editor              = \n| runtime             = 42\u201352 minutes<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fubo.tv/lp/series/17572093/|title=Dare Me|website=FuboTV|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n| company             = {{Plainlist|\n* Megan Abbott\n* Drowning Girl Productions\n* Fair Harbor Productions\n* Film 44\n* [[Universal Content Productions]]\n}}\n| distributor         = \n| picture_format      = [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n| first_aired         = {{Start date|2019|12|29}}\n| last_aired          = {{End date|present}}\n| website             = https://www.usanetwork.com/dare-me\n| website_title       = Official website\n| network             = [[USA Network]]\n| channel             = \n}}\n'''''Dare Me''''' is an American [[teen drama]] television series based on the [[Dare Me (novel)|novel of the same name]] by [[Megan Abbott]]. The series was picked up in late January 2019 and premiered on [[USA Network]] on December 29, 2019.<ref name=\"Premiere Date\"/>\n\n==Premise==\n''Dare Me'' follows the lives of competitive high school cheerleaders in \"a small Midwestern town\".<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n==Cast and characters==\n===Main===\n<!--Main cast order is according to original credits (the pilot episode). Do NOT rearrange cast order, per MOS:TVCAST. In addition, new main cast members will be at the bottom of the list.-->\n*[[Willa Fitzgerald]] as Coach Colette French,<ref name=\"auto\"/> Sutton Grove High School's new cheerleading coach\n*[[Herizen Guardiola]] as Addy Hanlon,<ref name=\"auto\"/> a cheerleader at Sutton Grove High School\n*Marlo Kelly as Beth Cassidy,<ref name=\"auto\"/> Addy's best friend and the captain of the cheer squad until Coach French eliminates the position\n*[[Rob Heaps]] as Matt French,<ref name=\"auto1\"/> Colette's husband and a project manager at Eagle Investments who is working on Sutton Grove High School's new stadium\n*[[Zach Roerig]] as Sarge Will Mosley,<ref name=\"auto1\"/> a local recruiter for the U.S. Marine Corps who is having an affair with Colette\n*[[Paul Fitzgerald (actor)|Paul Fitzgerald]] as Bert Cassidy,<ref name=\"auto1\"/> Beth's estranged father and the president of a real estate company named Eagle Investments\n*[[Alison Thornton]] as Tacy Cassidy,<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.usanetwork.com/dare-me/cast|title=Cast & Info {{!}} Dare Me|website=USA Network|language=en|access-date=January 2, 2020}}</ref> Beth's half-sister, and a freshman cheerleader on Sutton Grove High School's squad\n\n===Recurring===\n<!-- Reliably sourced and/or confirmed to make 4+ appearances in the series -->\n* Antonio J. Bell as Michael Slocum,<ref name=\"auto1\"/> Addy's friend\n* [[Amanda Brugel]] as Faith Hanlon,<ref name=\"AW&AB\"/> Addy's single mother who is a police officer\n* [[Tammy Blanchard]] as Lana Cassidy,<ref name=\"auto1\"/> Beth's mother\n* Tamberla Perry as J.J. Curtis,<ref name=\"auto1\"/> one of the local cheerleader boosters, and RiRi's mother\n* Adrian Walters as Jimmy Tibbs<ref name=\"AW&AB\"/>\n* [[Chris Zylka]] as Corporal Kurtz,<ref name=\"ChrisZ&TaveetaS\"/> a subordinate Marine recruiter of Sarge Will\n* Taveeta Szymanowicz as RiRi Curtis,<ref name=\"ChrisZ&TaveetaS\"/> a fellow member of the cheerleading team, and Addy and Beth's friend, and J.J.'s daughter\n*Addyson Douglas as Emily Diaz\n* [[Brittany Raymond]] as Cori Ross, a fellow member of the cheerleading team\n* Erika Prevost as Brianna Bradley, a fellow member of the cheerleading team\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table |background=#CE7DFD |overall= |title= |titleR= <ref name=\"Zap2It\"/> |director= |writer= |airdate= |airdateR=<ref name=\"Zap2It\">{{cite web|url= https://tvlistings.zap2it.com/overview.html?programSeriesId=SH03355606|title=Dare Me|work=[[Zap2It]]|accessdate=February 23, 2020}}</ref> |viewers= |country=U.S |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Coup d'\u00c9tat\n |DirectedBy      = Steph Green\n |WrittenBy       = [[Megan Abbott]] & Gina Fattore\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|12|29}}{{efn|name=OnlinePremiere|The episode was first released online on December 19, 2019.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=USA_Network|author=USA Network|number=1207729112166498304|title=Coach Colette French won't quit until her squad wins regionals. Watch the first episode of #DareMeTV before its premiere: https://usanet.tv/WatchDareMe|date=December 19, 2019|accessdate=December 19, 2019}}</ref>}}\n |Viewers         = 0.600<ref name=\"1.01\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzd